**Power of Attorney**

This Power of Attorney (this Power of Attorney) is made on [DATE] by [NAME OF PRINCIPAL] (hereinafter referred to as Principal).

**1. Grant of Power**

Principal hereby grants to [NAME OF ATTORNEY-IN-FACT] (hereinafter referred to as Agent), full power and authority to act on Principals behalf in all matters relating to:

* (a) Principals personal and business affairs;
* (b) Principals real and personal property;
* (c) Principals financial affairs;
* (d) Principals medical care and treatment;
* (e) Principals funeral arrangements; and
* (f) Any other matter that Principal may authorize in writing from time to time.

**2. Powers**

In particular, but without limiting the generality of the foregoing, Agent is authorized to:

* (a) Make, execute, and deliver all documents, instruments, and agreements in Principals name and on Principals behalf;
* (b) Borrow money, pledge Principals assets, and enter into contracts on Principals behalf;
* (c) Open and close bank accounts in Principals name;
* (d) Receive, disburse, and invest Principals funds;
* (e) Buy, sell, lease, and mortgage real property in Principals name;
* (f) Manage Principals businesses;
* (g) Make gifts on Principals behalf;
* (h) Elect to take or disclaim any inheritance or gift on Principals behalf;
* (i) Waive any right or claim of Principal;
* (j) File any legal action or proceeding on Principals behalf;
* (k) Represent Principal in any legal proceeding; and
* (l) Do all other acts and things necessary or desirable to carry out the purposes of this Power of Attorney.

**3. Limitations**

This Power of Attorney is not valid for the following purposes:

* (a) Creating or revoking a will;
* (b) Executing a deed of trust;
* (c) Creating a life estate;
* (d) Adopting a child; or
* (e) Any other act that Principal is prohibited from doing by law.

**4. Termination**

This Power of Attorney shall terminate upon the earliest to occur of the following events:

* (a) Principals death;
* (b) Principals revocation of this Power of Attorney in writing;
* (c) Agents death, incapacity, or resignation; or
* (d) [DATE] (the Termination Date).

**5. Governing Law**

This Power of Attorney shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of [STATE].

**IN WITNESS WHEREOF,** Principal has executed this Power of Attorney as of the date first written above.

[SIGNATURE OF PRINCIPAL]

[PRINTED NAME OF PRINCIPAL]
